# JavaScript standards

Full checklist: `docs/static-site-standards.md` (Vanilla JS, Browser APIs, theming, misc).

## Modules & loading

- ES modules only for new code; `export`/`import`
- Load with `type="module"` + `defer` (or `async` when order-independent)
- Do not extend `js/bundle-*.js` — add `js/feature-name.js` instead

## Patterns

- Event delegation on stable parents; `AbortController` to remove listeners
- Observers: IntersectionObserver (lazy/scroll), ResizeObserver, MutationObserver when needed
- Fetch for JSON/partials; `structuredClone`, optional chaining, nullish coalescing
- `matchMedia` for responsive JS; `requestAnimationFrame` / `requestIdleCallback` for work scheduling

## Web Components (when used)

- Custom Elements + Shadow DOM; clone from `<template>`
- File-per-component under `js/components/` (or similar)

## Theming / storage

- Theme toggle: CSS variables + `localStorage` key (e.g. `theme`) synced with `prefers-color-scheme`

## APIs (prefer native over libraries)

- History (`pushState` / `popstate`), Clipboard, Share (`navigator.share`), View Transitions, Web Animations

## Misc features

- Reading time calc, smooth anchor scroll, back-to-top — small dedicated modules
